---
title: Korean Beef Bibimbap with Zucchini, Mushrooms, and Carrots
description: This dish takes its name from the Korean word for mixing rice. Which is exactly what you’re meant to do after serving it: put your rice in a bowl, add the toppings, and mix it all together so that those flavors and textures combine in a glorious mishmash. There are plenty of flavors and textures going on here, too, like sweet carrot, juicy zucchini, and beef tossed with garlic, ginger, and soy.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5e285e954ed749220d6a77e8-8950518b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/korean-beef-bibimbap-5e285e954ed749220d6a77e8-f71932ff.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/korean-beef-bibimbap-5e285e954ed749220d6a77e8
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Korean
nutrition:
  calories: 840 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 37 g
  sodium: 1290 g
course: main course
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into thin half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel @carrots{6}; shave lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core. Discard core. Peel and mince @ginger{1%inch knob}. Mince @garlic cloves{2}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites with @white wine vinegar{5%tbsp} and a pinch of salt. Set aside to quick-pickle. In a separate small bowl, combine @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, half the @soy sauce{4%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and as much @sriracha sauce{2} as you like.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%tbsp} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add carrots and season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Add zucchini and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to bowl with carrots. Add mushrooms and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl with other veggies.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and ginger. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{20-30%seconds}. Add @ground beef{10%oz} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain any excess grease from pan. Increase heat to high and cook until browned, crisp, and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in remaining soy sauce and cook until mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; divide between #bowls{}. Arrange beef, zucchini, carrots, and mushrooms on top. Top with pickled scallion whites (draining first). Drizzle with sauce and any remaining sriracha to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.